From: NixBench contributors
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] xwayland: fall back when posix_fallocate is unsupported

NetBSD can provide posix_fallocate() while the filesystem backing
XDG_RUNTIME_DIR returns EOPNOTSUPP. Xwayland currently treats that as a fatal
shared-memory allocation error, causing Composite redirection to fail with
BadAlloc.

Fall back to ftruncate() for EOPNOTSUPP, matching the allocation used when
HAVE_POSIX_FALLOCATE is not defined. Preserve other posix_fallocate errors.
---
 hw/xwayland/xwayland-shm.c | 11 ++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/hw/xwayland/xwayland-shm.c b/hw/xwayland/xwayland-shm.c
--- a/hw/xwayland/xwayland-shm.c
+++ b/hw/xwayland/xwayland-shm.c
@@ -179,7 +179,16 @@ os_create_anonymous_file(off_t size)
     } while (ret == EINTR);
     OsReleaseSignals();
 
-    if (ret != 0) {
+    if (ret == EOPNOTSUPP) {
+        do {
+            ret = ftruncate(fd, size);
+        } while (ret == -1 && errno == EINTR);
+
+        if (ret < 0) {
+            close(fd);
+            return -1;
+        }
+    } else if (ret != 0) {
         close(fd);
         errno = ret;
         return -1;
-- 
2.50.1
